{
  "id": 933,
  "name": "Module 10: Introduction to modelling libraries in python",
  "visible": 1,
  "summary": "<div class=\"jumbotron jumbotron-fluid text-white shadow\" style=\"background: linear-gradient(to top,  var(--secondary), var(--primary),var(--info)); color: white; padding: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">\r\n    <h5></h5>\r\n    <div class=\"container\">\r\n        <p class=\"lead\"><span id=\"label_content_504745\"><strong><strong><span><span><span><span id=\"label_content_504745\">Module </span>Developer:&nbsp; Selina Ochukut</span></span></span><span><span><br></span></span></strong></strong></span></p>\r\n        <p><strong> Instructional Hours: </strong> 4 hours</p>\r\n        <hr class=\"my-4 border-white\">\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p></p>\r\n    <div class=\"box py-3 generalbox oukbook_content oukbook_introduction_chapter\">\r\n        <div class=\"oukbook_chapter_title_div\">\r\n            <div class=\"oukbook_chapter_booktitle2\" align=\"right\">DSC201: Python for Data Science</div>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div class=\"module-container\">\r\n            <div class=\"timeline\">\r\n                <div class=\"timeline-container primary\">\r\n                    <div class=\"timeline-icon\"><i class=\"fa fa-edit\"></i></div>\r\n                    <div class=\"timeline-body\">\r\n                        <h4 class=\"timeline-title\"><span class=\"badge\">Module Overview</span></h4>\r\n                        <p>This module provides an introduction to popular modeling libraries in Python, including Statsmodels, Scikit-learn (sklearn). You will learn about the capabilities and functionalities of each library and how to apply them for various machine learning and deep learning tasks.</p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"timeline-container danger\">\r\n                    <div class=\"timeline-icon\"><i class=\"fa fa-calendar-check-o\"></i></div>\r\n                    <div class=\"timeline-body\">\r\n                        <table class=\"custombox-definition\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n                            <tbody>\r\n                                <tr valign=\"top\">\r\n                                    <td class=\"custombox-header-thumb definition\" width=\"2%\"></td>\r\n                                    <td class=\"custombox-content definition\" width=\"98%\">\r\n                                        <div class=\"custombox-container definition\" style=\"padding-left: 10px;\">\r\n                                            <div class=\"custombox-flexline definition\">\r\n                                                <div class=\"custombox-header-caption definition\" width=\"98%\" style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n                                                    <h4>Learning Outcomes</h4>\r\n                                                </div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div class=\"custombox-flexline definition\">\r\n                                                <p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\"><span><strong></strong></span><span><strong>By the end of this module, you should be able to:</strong></span></p>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div class=\"custombox-flexline definition\">\r\n                                                <ol class=\"customlabel-subdefinition definition HELM_parts\" style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">\r\n                                                    <li><span> Describe the key functionalities and capabilities of the popular Python libraries</span></li>\r\n                                                    <li><span> Compare and contrast the different modeling libraries in Python.</span></li>\r\n                                                    <li><span> Use modelling libraries to implement basic machine learning applications to solve specific tasks.</span></li>\r\n                                                    <li><span> Assess the performance and suitability of models built using these libraries.</span></li>\r\n                                                </ol>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </td>\r\n                                </tr>\r\n                            </tbody>\r\n                        </table>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div></div>",
